          "j": 4,
          "n": 16,
          "note": "A_SP-prefix census L>70",
          "w": 2
        }
      ],
      "name": "ambient_L_le_70_and_L_le_2176",
      "statement": "Ambient free-1 multipad load (all fully D-split free-1 multi-mate highs, no j-fiber cut) is NOT bounded by 70 or by 2176 in general.",
      "status": "REFUTED"
    },
    "cover_load_not_R": {
      "name": "full_cover_L_core_le_R_false",
      "note": "Toys: L_cover_core can exceed R_toy while L_rep\u2264R_toy.",
      "statement": "L_cover_core(r) := #{H\u2208H_core: r\u2208cover(H)} is NOT bounded by R in general \u2014 a matched high can touch r via a mate V\u2260U_rep.",
      "status": "REFUTED"
    },
    "injection": {
      "name": "load_equals_active_e_sets_through_point",
      "proof": [
        "v25: root sets of H(X)+c for fixed high H are pairwise disjoint.",
        "So at most one U\u2208F_H contains r.",
        "Map high \u21a6 that U is injective on highs through r.",
        "U\\{r} is an (e\u22121)-subset of the remaining n\u22121 points."
      ],
      "statement": "For fixed domain index r: each free-1 high through r has exactly one active U\u220br (family disjointness, v25). Distinct highs \u21d2 distinct U. Hence L(r) \u2264 C(n\u22121, e\u22121). Deployed C(2097152-1, 67472-1) is huge \u2014 not a useful gate toward L\u226470.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "multimate": {
      "deployed": {
        "H_le": "n*L/(2e) \u2248 15.5409*L"
      },
      "name": "multimate_double_count",
      "proof": [
        "sum_H |cover(H)| = sum_r L(r) \u2264 n\u00b7L.",
        "sum_H |cover(H)| \u2265 2e\u00b7|H| under |F_H|\u22652 and disjoint U's."
      ],
      "statement": "If every counted high has |F_H|\u22652 (A_SP multi-mate), then |cover(H)|\u22652e and |H| \u2264 n\u00b7L/(2e). Deployed |H| \u2264 15.5\u00b7L (vs v38's |H|\u226431\u00b7L from |F_H|\u22651).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    }
  },
